- New but inappropriate page: if inappropriate because of spam or other clearly malicious content (evaluation is made by an Administrator), it is deleted right away; in the other cases, e.g. irrelevance to Arch, the article should be: marked with Template:Merge; or marked with Template:Redirect; or marked to be moved as a subpage of its author's User page with Template:Move (or moved right away).
- Old article become obsolete: mark with one of the following, in order of preference: Template:Merge; Template:Redirect; Template:Archive; wait at least 7 days; in absence of objecting discussions, or when these eventually resolve in favor of removal, perform the proposed action; when redirecting, consider following #Deal with talk pages after redirecting a page to another and #Fix double redirects; when archiving, follow the instructions in ArchWiki:Archive.

